Cleaning procedures in Excel
- Clean white spaces (TRIM)
- Select and treat all blanks or missing values
- Convert numbers stored as text into solely numbers
- Remove duplicates
- Highlight errors through conditional formatting
- Change casing (LOWER, UPPER, PROPER)
- Split data and merge (RIGHT, LEFT, MID, SPLIT, CONCATENATE)
- Delete irrelevant columns
- Spell check
- Delete all pre-existing formatting
- Use Find & Replace to clean data (REPLACE, SUBSTITUTE)
- Resize columns
- Rename columns
- Format data types
- Address outliers
- Delete hidden data
- Check for truncated entries and inconsistent entries
